# Portfolio Showroom Conventions

This is a public Astro site deployed to GitHub Pages (base `/portfolio`). The
Work page is a curated showroom driven by `projectOverrides` in
`src/data/projects.ts` — not a raw GitHub repo dump.

## Adding / editing a project

Each entry needs:
- `displayName`, `category`, `description`, `techStack`
- a demo target: internal `demoPath` (under `public/demos/...`) OR external
  `demoUrl` (full https). Use `#` / omit for no demo.
- `sourceUrl: ''` for private/local work (hides the GitHub link).

## Demo safety (critical)

- External `demoUrl`s must point at PUBLIC, browser-safe demos only.
- Never link to a local dev server, a tunnel URL (cloudflared/ngrok), or any
  app connected to private/local data. Those are not stable or safe to expose.
- The hover-preview iframe loads `demoUrl` live — confirm the target is meant
  to be embedded publicly.

## Build & ship

- `npm run build` must pass before pushing.
- Pushing to `main` triggers the GitHub Pages deploy — treat it as production.
- Internal links must use `withBase(...)`; external demos pass through as-is.
